# Next and React Safety

- Target the installed framework versions in this repo, not generic web examples.
- For uncertain Next.js behavior, consult local docs in `node_modules/next/dist/docs/`.
- Keep Server Component and Client Component boundaries explicit and intentional.
- Use `next/image`, `next/link`, and route handlers in idiomatic Next patterns.
- Avoid deprecated APIs and migration-era snippets from older Next versions.
- Keep data fetching and rendering patterns predictable and cache-aware.
- Prefer composition with small React components over large monolithic views.
